text.__SUMMARY__: Conasprella rainesae, common name Maze's cone,  is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails and their allies.Like all species within the genus Conasprella, these cone snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans, therefore live ones should be handled carefully or not at all.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Gulf of Mexico; in the Atlantic Ocean off Brasil.
text.Description: The maximum recorded shell length is 25 mm.
text.Habitat: Minimum recorded depth is 55 m. Maximum recorded depth is 110 m.
text.References: Puillandre N., Duda T.F., Meyer C., Olivera B.M. & Bouchet P. (2015). One, four or 100 genera? A new classification of the cone snails. Journal of Molluscan Studies. 81: 1-23
